ygData.msgSnippet: Actually I know Silvera and I believe every word of it...... I first ran into to her when she was 34th and in a group killing Sand Giants in Marr, I was 17th
ygData.messageBody:
Actually I know Silvera and I believe every word of it...... I first ran
into to her when she was 34th and in a group killing Sand Giants in Marr, I
was 17th and quite in awe (got some nice sketches though), Ive talked to her
several times, but now Im Hella Jealous........ :)-

Jaezebel Moonsong

Btw Tripped over your corpse on the EK bridge yesterday gave you a tell to
see if ya needed help, but you didnt answer....
-----Original Message-----
From: James Schuldes <jgs@...>
To: 'eqbards@onelist.com' <eqbards@onelist.com>
Date: Tuesday, July 20, 1999 11:45 AM
Subject: RE: [eqbards] Twinking


>From: James Schuldes <jgs@...>
>

>
>Here is the story:
>
>Late one night, early 4th of July weekend, me and couple of my fiends are
in
>Rivervale begging for a bind. I see Silvera Tinkerbelle who I know from a
>server email list and run over to say "hi I just wanted to meet you!" (She
>is lev 48 or 49 and I am impressed!) She actually talks to me and I nearly
>faint! Well, we do some duck dancing and other stoopid char tricks and
>generally hang out.
>
>Then she inspects my equipment and goes: "Greetings Sylly, looks like you
>could use some armor?" I say: "Well yes, if you know anyone selling
banded,
>I do have some plats saved up." She says come to the bank and lemme look
>what I might have... Then my trade screen come up and she drops in a couple
>of pieces of stuff I don't even recognize. Then she fills the trade screen
>and says 'take'
>
>At that point - I say to her "ya know I am way too low level for this..."
>And she says "I will understand if you say no..." But I think - hey this
is
>the chance of a life time! So I take!
>
>Then she fills the trade screen a second time and I am frantically looking
>to see if I got nuff slots and destroying all my food and beetle eyes. She
>says take.
>
